\end{align*}What is the remainder when $x$ is divided by $105$?

content.solution_latex:
If $x^2 - x + a$ divides $x^{13} + x + 90$, then the remainder when $x^{13} + x + 90$ is divided by $x^2 - x + a$ must be 0.
Performing the division, we get
$$\begin{array}{c|cc c cc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{x^{11}} &+ x^{10} &- 2 x^9 &+ 2 x^8 &- 2 x^7 &+ 2 x^6 &- 2 x^5 &+ 2 x^4 &- 2 x^3 &+ 2 x^2 &- 2 x &+ 2 \\
\cline{2-12}
x^2 - x + a & x^{13} &+ 0 x^{12} &+ 0 x^{11} &+ x^{10} &+ 0 x^9 &+ 0 x^8 &+ 0 x^7 &+ 0 x^6 &+ 0 x^5 &+ 0 x^4 &+ x^3 &+ x^2 &+ 0 x^1 &+ 90 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{x^{13}} &- x^{12} &+ x^{11} \\
\cline{2-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{0} &+ x^{12} &- 2 x^{11} &+ x^{10} \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} &+ x^{12} &- x^{11} &+ x^{10} \\
\cline{3-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} &0 &- x^{11} &+ 0 x^{10} &- 2 x^9 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & &- x^{11} &+ x^{10} &- x^9 \\
\cline{4-6}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & &0 &0 &- x^9 &+ 2 x^8 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & &- x^9 &+ x^8 &- x^7 \\
\cline{5-7}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & &0 &x^8 &- x^7 &+ x^6 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & &+ x^8 &- x^7 &+ x^6 \\
\cline{6-8}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & &0 &0 &0 &- x^5 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & & &- x^5 &+ x^4 &- x^3 \\
\cline{7-9}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & & & & x^4 &- x^3 &+ x^2 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & & & & + x^4 &- x^3 &+ x^2 \\
\cline{8-10}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & & & & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\
\end{array}$$
Since the remainder is 0, we see that $a = \boxed{2}$.
The answer is: 2

